article.headline: Stephen F.Austin 92, Texas Wesleyan 42
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas -- Josh Alexander scored 20 points and grabbed 10 rebounds to lead Stephen F. Austin to a 92-42 win over Texas Wesleyan on Saturday night. Three players scored in double digits for the Lumberjacks (4-2). Jereal Scott scored 16, Matt Kingsley scored 13 and Eddie Williams added 11. Alexander was the game's leading scorer and rebounder. Chris Berry was the high scorer for Texas Wesleyan (5-2) with 10 points. Ryan Barnes pulled down the most rebounds for the Rams with five. The Lumberjacks made 55 percent of their shots and were 23-of-35 from the free throw line.
